  "text": "The datasource plugin query path in Grafana consists of multiple layers orchestrating the flow from an HTTP request through plugin dispatch to response transformation.\n\n**HTTP Request Handler Entry Point**: The query request enters through `/pkg/api/ds_query.go` where `QueryMetricsV2()` handles incoming query requests. This function delegates to `queryDataService` (the query service) after binding and validating the request. The endpoint can be rewritten to the new query service API if `FlagQueryServiceRewrite` feature flag is enabled via `getDSQueryEndpoint()`.\n\n**Core Query Service**: `/pkg/services/query/query.go` contains the main `ServiceImpl` which implements the `Service` interface with `QueryData()` and `QueryDataNew()` methods. The service processes requests by:\n- Parsing the request into datasource-grouped queries via `parseMetricRequest()`\n- Handling expression queries via `handleExpressions()`\n- Executing single datasource queries via `handleQuerySingleDatasource()`\n- Executing multiple datasource queries concurrently via `executeConcurrentQueries()`\n\n**Plugin Manager Dispatch**: The `/pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go` implements `QueryData()` which looks up the plugin from the registry via `s.plugin()` and dispatches the query request to the plugin's QueryData method. It handles error cases and ensures response frames have refId set.\n\n**Backend Plugin Clients**: \n- `/pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go` provides `QueryData()` which converts backend requests to gRPC protobuf format, calls the remote plugin via gRPC, and converts responses back from protobuf\n- `/pkg/plugins/backendplugin/coreplugin/core_plugin.go` wraps core (built-in) plugins, implementing `QueryData()` which delegates to the `QueryDataHandler` if available\n\n**Plugin Registry**: `/pkg/plugins/backendplugin/coreplugin/registry.go` registers all core datasource plugins (Prometheus, Loki, PostgreSQL, etc.) by wrapping them with `asBackendPlugin()`.\n\n**Query Service API Server**: `/pkg/registry/apis/query/` provides a Kubernetes-style API server:\n- `query.go` implements the REST storage layer with a `Connect()` method that acts as a POST handler for the query endpoint, calling `handleQuery()` which orchestrates the flow\n- `register.go` defines `QueryAPIBuilder` which sets up the API server and registers routes\n- `client/plugin.go` implements `QueryData()` that converts k8s-style requests to backend format and dispatches to plugins\n- `plugins.go` manages plugin registry/discovery for the API\n\n**Aggregator Plugin Handler**: `/pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go` provides `QueryDataHandler()` as an HTTP handler that processes query requests in the aggregator, converting query data requests and dispatching to the plugin client.\n\n**Response Transformation**: \n- `/pkg/expr/query_convert.go` with `ConvertBackendRequestToDataRequest()` converts backend query requests to k8s experimental API format\n- `/pkg/promlib/querydata/response.go` implements response parsing with `parseResponse()` which converts HTTP responses to backend DataResponse format\n\n**Datasource Implementations**: Specific datasources like `/pkg/tsdb/prometheus/prometheus.go` implement the datasource plugin interface by delegating to the promlib service (`/pkg/promlib/library.go`), which uses the custom query execution in `/pkg/promlib/querydata/request.go`'s `Execute()` method.\n\n**Client Middleware**: Query requests flow through middleware in `/pkg/services/pluginsintegration/clientmiddleware/` including caching, metrics, logging, and tracing middleware that enrich the request/response cycle.\n\n**API Types**: `/pkg/apis/query/v0alpha1/query.go` defines `QueryDataRequest` and `QueryDataResponse` types that wrap the backend SDK types with Kubernetes metadata.\n\nThe complete flow: HTTP Request → API Handler → Query Service → Plugin Manager → Backend Plugin Client → Datasource Implementation → Response Parsing → Response Transformation → HTTP Response."
}

